   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Hover over the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Playbook</uicontrol> tab and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Clauses</uicontrol> to display a list of clauses in your library.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Scroll to the place in your document where you want to insert the clause. Place your cursor at the point of insertion.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="434"
                         href="../attachments/45220128/49676323.png"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the <image placement="inline"
                      width="20"
                      href="../attachments/45220128/49676324.png"
                      id="image_apr_3gq_12c"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Insert Clause</uicontrol> icon to insert the clause into your
               document.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="648"
                         href="../attachments/45220128/49676325.png"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The inserted clause is automatically marked as a smart clause (shown with a grey
            border). You can go to <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Document </uicontrol>
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Clauses</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> in the X-Author pane to confirm the clause is now recognized in the
            document. If you decide you want to remove clause properties and revert the clause to
            static text, use the Document panel to <xref href="../working_with_clauses_4522_45220112/to_unmark_a_clause.dita#t298ED1A-BDF2-11F0-1430-09173F13E4C5"
                  class="- topic/xref ">unmark the clause</xref>. When you check in the document, any smart clauses can be
            reconciled to the agreement and information for the inserted clause is added to the
            Agreement Clause related list on the agreement record.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To learn how the Agreement Clause related list is populated with each insert, modify and
            delete action, refer to <xref href="../tracking_clauses_in_your__45220100/45220100.dita"
                  format="dita"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
         <note type="warning" class="- topic/note ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">At this time, clauses can only be inserted in documents with "Full Access" protection.</p>
         </note>
      </postreq>
